               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18360201-name-1114" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18360201-name-1114" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360201-name-1114" type="surname" value="NARBROUGH"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360201-name-1114" type="given" value="EDWARD"></interp>EDWARD NARBROUGH</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a brass-founder. The prisoner was in my employ—about nine o'clock, on the 12th of January, as he was going away, in consequence of information, I said I wanted him—he said, "What for?—I said I thought he had something about him that did not belong to him—he turned round, and made towards the street-door—I had fastened that. and he could not get out—he said, "I want a drop of water"—he went to the water-bull, and I after him, and he dropped this pattern.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18360201-name-1115" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18360201-name-1115" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360201-name-1115" type="surname" value="GREEN"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360201-name-1115" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN GREEN</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a policeman. I was called in, and took the prisoner and the pattern.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner</hi>. Mrs. Bennet asked me to go into the shop, and get a towel,</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183602010197"></xptr>
               <p>and I asked her if I should bring a pattern out—she said I might if I liked, and I said I would.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18360201-name-1116" type="witnessName">
